         <abstract id="aspace_b21fbd4f5cd7aaab4cbdca63950897c2">Fred Chappell is an author and a
            poet, and is a retired English professor from the University of North Carolina at
            Greensboro. Dabney Stuart is also an author and poet, and is a retired English professor
            at Washington and Lee University in Lexington, Virginia. Accession (2009-0211) (150
            items; 0.6 lin. ft.; dated 1984-2009) consists of Fred Chappell's letters to Dabney
            Stuart, covering a wide range of topics from personal stories and updates on families to
            his musings on literature and poetry in general. Chappell frequently offers feedback on
            Stuart's latest writings, as well as seeks input from Stuart on his own work.
            Occassional drafts are included for Stuart to read.</abstract>
